# gRPC-Web Example

## Overview
This example demonstrates how to use gRPC-Web with httpyac.
gRPC-Web allows you to call gRPC services from environments that don't support HTTP/2 or native gRPC.

## Prerequisites
1. Load proto file definitions first
2. gRPC-Web service must be running and accessible

## Basic gRPC-Web Request

### Load proto file
# @proto ./path/to/your/service.proto

### Make a gRPC-Web request using GRPC_WEB keyword
GRPC_WEB localhost:8080/helloworld.Greeter/SayHello
Content-Type: application/grpc-web+proto

{
  "name": "World"
}

###

### Alternative syntax using grpc-web:// protocol
grpc-web://localhost:8080/helloworld.Greeter/SayHello

{
  "name": "HttpYac User"
}

###

### gRPC-Web with custom headers
GRPC_WEB example.com/myservice.MyService/MyMethod
Authorization: Bearer token123
Custom-Header: value

{
  "field1": "value1",
  "field2": 42
}

###

## Notes
- gRPC-Web uses HTTP POST with application/grpc-web+proto content-type
- Messages are encoded using protobuf (same as regular gRPC)
- Supports both unary and server-streaming calls
- Works through HTTP proxies and in restricted network environments
- Use GRPC for native gRPC, GRPC_WEB for gRPC-Web

## Differences from regular GRPC
- gRPC-Web uses HTTP/1.1 compatible transport
- Works in browser environments and through HTTP proxies
- Binary data is base64 encoded in text mode
- Limited to unary and server-streaming (no client-streaming or bidirectional)

## URL Format
grpc-web://[protocol://]<server>[/path]/<service>/<method>

Examples:
- grpc-web://localhost:8080/mypackage.MyService/MyMethod
- GRPC_WEB https://api.example.com/grpc/mypackage.MyService/MyMethod
- grpc-web://example.com:443/path/to/service/MyService/MyMethod
